==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Outlay
<hw>Out*lay"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To lay out; to
spread out; to display.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Drayton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outlay</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Outlay
<hw>Out"lay`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A laying
out or expending.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is expended; expenditure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An outlying haunt.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outleap</ent>⟦br⟧
